{"TopicId":33829,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"[Seal Aerospace] Transport Rover Mini","CreatedByName":"ShachonianX","CreatedById":62805,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-19T19:20:13Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ShachonianX","CreatedById":62805,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-19T19:20:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://imageshack.us/a/img850/1774/screenshot16ds.png\u0022 alt=\u0022screenshot16ds.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://imageshack.us/a/img69/2810/sealaerospaceflag2.png\u0022 alt=\u0022sealaerospaceflag2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIsn\u0027t it annoying when your rover design flips over? Well, this here rover doesn\u0027t flip over at all! It has room for one Kerbal, and can be used to travel all across Kerbin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDownload Link: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://kerbalbase.net23.net/submission/15\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://kerbalbase.net23.net/submission/15\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-06-19T21:40:03Z\u0022 title=\u002206/19/2013 09:40  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002211 yr\u0022\u003EJune 19, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by ShachonianX\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zekes","CreatedById":23840,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-19T19:35:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ehow stable is it?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ShachonianX","CreatedById":62805,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-19T19:38:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022zekes\u0022 data-cite=\u0022zekes\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003Ehow stable is it?\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI haven\u0027t had any problems with stability at all with it.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Naf5000","CreatedById":17119,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-19T21:36:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIn my experience, car-sized rovers made with medium wheels have exceptional stability. I had an open-bed kerbal transport that could safely go 17 mps without flipping on even (KSC) terrain, and that one had a center of mass far from where I wanted it. This thing could probably drive down a Mohole safely, provided you armor the extremely fragile cabin.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Error","CreatedById":58941,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-20T14:45:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYeah, the only issue is that the 1-man lander can will go pop if you poke it the wrong way.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}